<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="638" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,775,926,1167]" pageId="7" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[174,291,926,949]" pageId="7" pageNumber="638">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae longer than body; segment Iat least 3 times the length of the head; bases of segment I widely separated, segment IV spatulate; hood well developed, compressed; three cephalic spines, occipital pair very long reaching the bases of segment I; pronotum with three high carinae and areolated; lateral pronotal carinae fully developed; lateral margins of hemelytra serrated and with setae.
</paragraph>
